# =============================================================================
# stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.py  ·  Flood Data Pipeline — Query CC Parquet Index
# =============================================================================
# Drop-in alternative to stage_02_query_cc_index.py for use when
# index.commoncrawl.org (the CDX API server) is down.
#
# HOW IT WORKS (different from stage_02):
#   stage_02  → hits the CDX HTTP API at index.commoncrawl.org
#   stage_02b → queries the columnar Parquet index hosted on data.commoncrawl.org
#               (the same S3-backed CDN that serves WARC files — currently up)
#               Uses DuckDB + httpfs to query remotely with predicate pushdown.
#               DuckDB reads row-group statistics to skip most data — it does NOT
#               download the full 250 GB of parquet files per crawl.
#
# EFFICIENCY NOTE:
#   The Parquet files are sorted by url_surtkey (= SURT-form URL, sorted
#   alphabetically by reversed domain). This means for any given registered
#   domain the relevant rows are clustered in a small number of row groups.
#   DuckDB skips all other row groups automatically via min/max statistics.
#   Expect ~1–5 MB of actual data transferred per domain per crawl file,
#   not the full 800 MB per file.
#
# OUTPUT:
#   Identical schema to stage_02. Downstream stages (03, 04, 05, 06) are
#   unaffected — just point them at the same cc_index_hits.parquet.
#
#   output/cc_index_hits.parquet       (same schema as stage_02)
#   output/hit_count_summary.parquet   (same schema as stage_02)
#   raw_index_responses/parquet_{crawl_id}_{flood_id}.jsonl   (raw saves)
#   logs/stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.log
#
# DEPENDENCIES:
#   pip install duckdb pandas pyarrow
#   (boto3 NOT required — file listing uses CC's published HTTP manifest)
#
# Run:
#   python stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.py              # pilot events only
#   python stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.py --all        # Phase 2 full run
#   python stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.py --flood-id 3 # single event debug
#   python stage_02b_query_cc_parquet.py --crawl CC-MAIN-2024-46  # one crawl only
#
# SWITCHING BACK:
#   To return to stage_02 once index.commoncrawl.org recovers:
#     1. Delete raw_index_responses/   (or just let stage_02 overwrite)
#     2. Run python stage_02_query_cc_index.py as normal
#   The cc_index_hits.parquet schema is identical so nothing else changes.
# =============================================================================

